The paper discusses improving search performance on Flickr by personalizing search results based on user metadata. This involves filtering tag search results by user's contacts or a larger social network, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also describes a probabilistic model that takes advantage of tag information to discover latent topics contained in the search results, which could fall under the categories of social networks (cs.SI), multimedia (cs.MM), and machine learning (cs.SD). Finally, the paper mentions using tags to describe users' interests, which could also fall under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL).
